cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about saliency detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a unified framework that uses weak supervision sources, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions caption generation, which falls under natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing, which is a subfield of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
